t813.text: Dizzy Miss Lizzy HARD cut to Clarice flawlessly living her best life (shopping, excelling at work etc.) as Duncan is singing about her. Their lives are great Fin.

t814.text: Yesterday Annie had enough and left Winifred. He’s alone and finds an old VHS tape titled “Winifred and Clarice’s wedding”. He plays it and sings of easier times and how life was better before he screwed it all up.

t815.text: I’ve Just Seen A Face Clarice enjoys the serenade and agrees to go on a date with him. They hit it off and Duncan sings as they pass through months of dating.

t816.text: Tell Me What You See Duncan surprises Clarice at her new address, with a serenade of this song outside her window. He asks her on a date.

t817.text: You Like Me Too Much Annie singing about their relationship with Winifred

t818.text: It’s Only Love ~Hard cut to months down the track~ Winifred and Annie are always arguing and Winifred secretly doesn’t feel the same reassurance as he did when he was with Clarice... He thinks maybe she was really ~the one~ for him and he really fucked up.

t819.text: Act Naturally Clarice singing on the train about having to act naturally even though she’s heartbroken inside.

t820.text: Ticket To Ride Duncan told Clarice about the affair and she’s embarrassed and heartbroken. Winifred sings as he sees Clarice get on a train, leaving him forever (could be a duet, bouncing back and forth from Winifred and Clarice... idk).

t821.text: You’re Gonna Lose That Girl Winifred’s best friend (let’s call him Duncan) who has a crush on Clarice, finds out about the affair and sings out his feelings.

t822.text: Another Girl It’s a month later. Winifred tries to stay faithful, but falls for ~another girl~ (let’s call her Annie).

t823.text: I Need You Clarice emotionally sings about how much she loves Winifred and begs him to please give their relationship another shot. He agrees.

t824.text: You’ve Got To Hide Your Love Away Partner 2 (we’ll call her Clarice) sings about a previous relationship that hurt her so much that she hasn’t opened up to anyone since, except Winifred.

t825.text: The Night Before Partner 1 (let’s call him Winifred ) reminisces about the early days of their relationship and how things have changed.

t826.text: Help! A couple start off together, young, lovey dovey, singing the song happily at each other. The song slowly goes through their life until they’re fighting and singing about their bumpy relationship. They both storm off into different rooms of their house.
